&lt;h1&gt;Fire Safety Manager&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;£31,365-£37,890 (Band 6)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;Permanent - 37.5 hours per week&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TheFire Safety Managerwill be responsible for providing specialist guidance and support to Managers and Staff within the Isle of Wight NHS Trust in relation to the risk management of fire safety.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to manage, organise, implement, co-ordinate and maintain full and efficient fire prevention, fire precautions and the training of staff in all premises managed by the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will provide specialist advice to design consultants and colleagues in respect of statutory structural fire safety in existing buildings and planning of new buildings incorporating HTM 05 (Fire Code) requirements, at both design and construction stages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for ensuring and providing all Trust Staff has access to Fire Safety training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will ensure compliance with relevant Legislation, Regulation, Healthcare Technical Memorandum (HTM), Code of Practice and Technical Guidance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information, please contact Rob Graham on robert.graham12@nhs.net or01983 534869&lt;/p&gt;
